docs.lead_paragraph: A poorly-clad and miserable-looking man, whose name is unknown, was found dead and half hidden in the weeds in a vacant lot at the corner of Conduit and Railroad Avenues, East New-York, yesterday morning. About two hours before he had robbed the butcher's shop of Frederick Nicholaus, on Crescent Street, of all the knives and cleavers it contained.

headline.main: FOUND DEAD WITH HIS PLUNDER.; A Brooklyn Burglar Robs a Store and Soon Afterward Dies of Heart Disease.

docs.lead_paragraph: I have always been deemed handsome, so universally so that I have never considered the fact, for conceit hath its source in doubt. Some men are born so ugly that their comeliness, which is the gift of years, remains a matter of surprise. Others start from infancy with an evanescent beauty which becomes a reminiscence to their kindred, and a secret faith to themselves.
